Putting out hooks and looking up sources on art you like is how one finds artists that can do what you want. If you don't put a bit of time in here and there building up watchlists, you'll stay at the point of not having any idea of where to start. It's not instant gratification, but neither is commissioning. You often have to wait months because of queues or artists having lives. Sometimes your artist will literally be homeless for a few months and struggle to get back to drawing anything, but if you really like their work then it's worth the wait, especially if they're obviously going through shit and aren't being scammers.

tl;dr art and opportunities don't just fall into your lap. If you care about getting art you have to put time in or get really goddamn lucky.
